Three men have been arrested by Mountain Rise police after they allegedly robbed two Honchos franchise employees at gunpoint on Monday afternoon. The two employees were robbed just after making a delivery on Dr Chota Motala Road. According to a statement released by the Mountain Rise police, the employees were robbed at gunpoint while they were in their delivery vehicle. "The robbers stole R2900 from one of the employees and his wallet. The men then removed the keys from the ignition and ran on foot before getting into a vehicle which had been waiting for them," read the statement. One of the employees recognised one of the suspects as an ex-employee of Honchos and informed police of this. Members of the Mountain Rise crime prevention unit followed up on the information and three suspects were arrested. The vehicle used in the offence was seized. A gas gun, samsung cellphone and an undisclosed amount of cash was recovered.